txt.en: Collected crates of stolen belongings at Bolg Maufulug ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
The Orcs of Moria have begun mustering in Fanuidhol in preparation to assault Lothl√≥rien.

'Your efforts on behalf of my fellow marchwardens are commendable, [placeholder], but alas, the Orcs of Moria continue to pour out of the Black Hole and my kinsmen continue to perish from Middle-earth.

'I must ask you to sally forth once more into Bolg Maufulug and defeat the foe there. If you should find any more belongings stolen from the fallen Elves, please bring those to me as well, so that they can be returned to the families of the lost.

'Bolg Maufulug lies to the west and a little north of here. Anything you bring back will be greatly appreciated.'

Bolg Maufulug lies to the west and a little north from Talan Fanuidhol.\n\nBahanneth has asked you to enter Bolg Maufulug and defeat the Orcs there. He has also asked you to collect any stolen belongings you find as well.
'You have done well, [placeholder]. The Orcs have suffered another defeat at your hands, and the Galadhrim will benefit from the recovery of their kinsmen's belongings.'
Bahanneth is at Talan Fanuidhol, east and a little south of Bolg Maufulug.\n\nYou should return to Bahanneth with the stolen belongings you recovered and news of your victory against the Orcs.
'The Galadhrim will be grateful for any assistance to us that you can grant against the Orcs of Moria. Any stolen belongings you can recover for us would be much appreciated as well.'
'Have you not done as I asked, [placeholder]? There are many Orcs to defeat and many stolen belongings to recover at Bolg Maufulug.'
Collect crates of stolen belongings at Bolg Maufulug ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
Bring the stolen belongings to Bahanneth at Talan Fanuidhol
